definitions.definition: A person , animal or plant living at a certain location or in a certain area .
A bird which does not migrate during the course of the year.
A physician receiving specialized medical training.
examples: She's a resident in neurosurgery at Mass General.

definitions.definition: A diplomatic representative who resides in a foreign country , usually of inferior rank to an ambassador .
A legal permanent resident , someone who maintains residency .
